## 🎯 Key Takeaways for Interview

```
1. GREEDY INSIGHT:
   → Buy cheapest first to MAXIMIZE count

2. COUNTING SORT USE CASE:
   → Use when values are in LIMITED RANGE (here 1 to 10^5)
   → Avoids O(n log n) comparison sort → O(n + M)

3. BATCH DUPLICATE HANDLING:
   → can_buy = min(freq[price], coins // price)
   → This single line handles ALL bars of same price!

4. WHEN TO USE WHICH:
   → Comparison Sort: Simple, works always, O(n log n)
   → Counting Sort:   When range is small, O(n + M)
```

